Sebastien Haller has taken the 2021/22 edition of the Champions League by storm in his debut season in European football’s top club tournament for Ajax. At the age of 27, the former West Ham man has established himself as one of the finest strikers in Europe this term, as no player has managed to score as many times as he has netted in the Champions League. Haller is currently the tournament’s top scorer with 11 goals, ahead of Robert Lewandowski  and Mohamed Salah .   Emery: Difficult to coach Neymar, Kylian Mbappe     West Ham gets tough Sevilla draw for last 16     OLD ENEMIES: Tuchel, Klopp in titanic Carabao Cup battle   The 11 goals in his first seven Champions League games have helped him become the player with the best start to the competition. To put it in perspective, it took Erling Haaland nine games to reach the same tally. Haller has managed to get his name on the scoresheet in all the Champions League games he has played, scoring home and away against Sporting CP, Borussia Dortmund and Besiktas, as well as away at Benfica. Only Cristiano Ronaldo had celebrated at least one goal in each of his six group stage games back in 2017/18 with Real Madrid. The Portuguese star scored in 11 consecutive games between 2017 and 2018. The Ajax striker is scoring one goal every 49 minutes in the Champions League and no footballer has been able to keep up with his pace in Europe. Meanwhile, Haller he is celebrating a goal every 83 minutes across all competitions with Ajax.